        <updateDate>2003-08-27T16:44:00Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Home Lead Safety Tax Credit Act of 2003 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to provide owners of residential properties built in the United States before 1978 with a tax credit for lead-based paint abatement costs performed by a certified lead abatement contractor (50 percent of the cost of the abatement, not to exceed $1,500 per dwelling unit).</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
